Source: git-reword
Section: devel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Lenik <git-reword@bodz.net>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), python3
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/lenik/git-reword

Package: git-reword
Architecture: all
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, git, python3-git-filter-repo
Description: Reword git commit messages from files in a directory
 git-reword allows you to reword multiple git commit messages by preparing
 new messages in files named after the commits. This is useful for batch
 rewriting commit messages in a repository.
 .
 The package includes:
  - git-reword: Main utility to reword commit messages
  - gentestrepo: Generate test git repositories
  - genrewords: Generate messagedir with reword files

